text.tspan: Various measures of national saving/investment compared to GDP (per
capita, in international dollars), United Kingdom, 1900 to 2000
GDP (gross domestic product) represents a nation's total income. The rest of the variables are various measures of national
saving and investment, or in other words, changes in total wealth. In order of increasing comprehensiveness, these measures
include: Net investment = net fixed produced capital formation and overseas investment; Green investment = Net investment +
change in natural capital; Genuine savings = Green investment + education expenditure; GSTFP = Genuine savings + Net
present value of total factor productivity (i.e. technological change).
